I think it's not as simple as the "Mean/Median" over Nth Percentile as the graph shows, because the gas distribution is somewhat bi-modal: the first couple transactions in a block will pay a lot because of arbitrage opportunities. It'd be interesting to analyze the following:
- Those "tail" txns aside, how does the mean/median over 10th percentile value change; 
- Pre and post-1559, what % of transaction fees come from the "tail" values
